gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: TREES_BIG2005_IN is a point shapefile showing the locations of state champion trees in Indiana. The register is updated every 5 years. Each location represents a native tree that is the largest individual of its species found in Indiana. These locations are based on detailed records of the Indiana Big Tree Register 2005 and locations were digitized using 7.5 minute U.S. Geological Survey quadrangle maps, various aerial photographic data, streets, hydrology, and town layers for reference. Tree measurements are includeded in the attributes.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This dataset was compiled to create a GIS layer of champion tree locations in Indiana. It is intended for a variety of uses by the public recognizing that the horizontal accuracy does not support high precision applications.

gmd:credit.gco:CharacterString: Data is from IDNR, Forestry Division, 2005 Indiana Big Tree Register

gmd:measureDescription.gco:CharacterString: All trees listed in the published 2005 Register have been included.

The attributes were assigned to each point location as they are recorded in the Indiana Big Tree Register 2005 and Big Tree Nomination forms. Measurements come from nomination forms and may differ slightly from the registry book. Scientific names were not spell checked. Information came predominately from tree nomination forms, not the published registry book.

The accuracy for each point is considered very good. Each point was located by referencing roads, hydrology, towns, land sections, U.S. Geological Survey quadrangles, and aerial photography. Positions are dependent on maps and directions provided on Nomination forms.
The vertical positional accuracy was not a factor in the production of this shapefile.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Big Tree nomination forms were obtained for all Big Trees in the Register that occur in Indiana. The nomination form maps were used to locate each tree by referencing other data layers and landmarks. Measurements for each tree were entered in the database attributes.

TREES_BIG2000_IN was used as a base layer to update new champions for 2005. The same Nomination forms, obtained in 2000 and new nomination forms in 2005 were used. The same methods were replicated. Almost all information in the shapefile was obtained from the nomination forms rather that the the published book, so some minor discrepancies exist.

This metadata file was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit, v. 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser, v. 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (U.S. Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected, except that no values were assigned to "Abscissa_Resolution" and "Ordinate_Resolution."
Digital Data of Big Tree Champions for 2000.
